This paper deals with the privacy concerns related to web query log data, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The most likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases), as the paper presents a novel transaction anonymization technique. The second likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), as the paper deals with privacy concerns and re-identification of users. The third likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as the paper deals with web query logs. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper uses clustering techniques. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.CY (Computers and Society), as the paper deals with the ethical and social implications of releasing web query log data.
